node.text: Are they safe though after being released?
Well when the tourist come back again they will be gone:(
@laohus this was actually the situation in Thailand before these elephant parks opened up. You can watch AJ+ video on yt to learn more
@laohus hihi fellow elephant carer! Every bit of awareness helps and there are many people trying to give them the best! Do check out https://www.saveelephant.org/

😭 Actually there’s a video from another news channel that explains why this is a really bad thing. There is very little natural forest left in Thailand, not enough for so many elephants. Most of these “tourist parks” allow them to feed and care for the elephant including frequent vet visits. Closure of the parks means that instead of returning to the forests, the elephants may be taken to the city to perform and hope to make money there - which is very dangerous for their welfare and stresses them out

@kelemel_ Please do look into the website and all their projects, if you are able to, you can sponsor an elephant or even an open donation which all goes into the habitat of their sanctuaries and to protect them. YES there are trips for human interaction but they are limited and also not abused for our entertainment value!! There's always a way to help them!! 🐘🐘🐘

Hihi, to those who actually did their research and knows the real reasons for their release (eg, not enough money to maintain them, and the effects captivity has on them) let's cut the crap of "this isn't good news cause I KNOW the real reason". Instead let's spread awareness of genuine places that care for them and not capitalize on them entertaining us! Please make sure to also research on ways to HELP them! Cause donations do matter, but so does awareness that there are ways to help them!! Do check out https://www.saveelephant.org/
Finally this is a good new I always waiting to hear about it
